==English==

===Adjective===
'''bubbly''' ({{compar}} '''bubblier''', {{superl}} '''bubbliest''')

#Full of [[bubble]]s.
#:''Whip the egg white into a bubbly froth.''
#(''colloquial'') Cheerful, lively.
#:''She has a bubbly personality.''

===Noun===
'''bubbly''' (''uncountable'')

#(''informal'') [[Champagne]].
#:''We're getting married - this calls for a bottle of bubbly!''

